article.description: Mason Faulkner had 22 points as Western Carolina defeated Gardner-Webb 71-59 on Saturday.
article.headline: Faulkner leads W. Carolina over Gardner-Webb 71-59
article.linkText: Faulkner leads W. Carolina over Gardner-Webb 71-59
article.story: CULLOWHEE, N.C. -- Mason Faulkner had 22 points as Western Carolina defeated Gardner-Webb 71-59 on Saturday. Carlos Dotson had 15 points and eight rebounds for Western Carolina (1-1). Kameron Gibson added 13 points. Xavier Cork had nine rebounds for the hosts. Eric Jamison had 15 points and seven rebounds for the Runnin' Bulldogs (0-2). Jose Perez added 13 points and seven rebounds. Western Carolina matches up against NC A&T at home on Tuesday. Gardner-Webb takes on North Carolina on the road on Friday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
